venue.name: Nice Côte d'Azur Airport (NCE) (Aéroport Nice Côte d'Azur (NCE))

formattedAddress: Departure Transit Lounge, Level 3, Terminal 1 (Changi International Airport)

tip.text: The spaghetti with cod roe sauce is a must do. The 6.8 rating currently is undeserved. Don't go for the sushi 🍣 here. Excellent is the Daikon salad, Edamame, deep fried lotus root, Houjicha green tea
Try the Chateaubriand. Amazing! So many wonderful items. The Ox tongue, kimichi, any Wagyu, Hokkaido gelato 🍧 If you're into Kobe, this is your place
Try the Dim Sum (Hong Kong style served here) like the crispy rice roll, spinach tofu and if you are into it, the chicken feet. I see this place as quite complementary to #dintaifung

venue.name: La Concha Beach (Playa de La Concha / Kontxa Hondartza)

tip.text: One of the best dishes in the Basque region is the cod cheeks ( Kokotxas ). @CasaGandarias serves my favorite recipe #mustdo
If by chance you can have Sunday lunch here, definitely go for the Cozinho a Portuguesa dish. This is certainly not Lightfare but robustly satisfying. The desserts here are also to die for
Recommendable if you want to brave trying the lamprey eel. Otherwise not on the same level as other nearby seafood marisquerias in Matosinhos
Try one of the monster crabs 🦀 here. Very upscale professional seafood restaurant. Appreciate the smoking room to have a nice cigar and Brandie before commencing with a dessert
I've got two words for you here and they are 'Conga Hotdog'. Topped with melted cheese, Bifana pork and the Conga special sauce, this my friends is unmissable
Gorgeous Bifana sandwich can be readily enjoyed here with a nice mug of house wine
